```latex
\documentclass[tikz,border=10pt]{standalone}
\usepackage{amssymb}
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
  % Left figure
  \draw (0,0) -- (1,0) -- (1,2) -- (0.2,1.2) -- (0,1) -- (0,0);

  % Right figure
  \draw (3,0) .. controls (3,1) and (3,1) .. (3,2) .. controls (4,3) and (5,3) .. (6,2) .. controls (7,1) and (7,1) .. (6,0) -- (3,0);
  \fill (4.5,1) circle (0.05);
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

This code constructs two figures:
- The left figure is a polygon with five sides.
- The right figure consists of a shape with rounded bottom edges and includes a dot at the interior point. 

The use of `controls` in the `\draw` command creates smooth curves for the rounded parts of the shape.

